                </step:σ>
            </future>
        <present>
            In sum, I fear that I am proving to be unequal to the demands of practical reason
            <_>
                I fear that I am losing my grip on reason, letting it slip away
                <_ cog:link='/theorist/ethics/moral_matter/#R'/>
                <_ cog:link='#experience'/>
                <_>One’s most cherished value and frequent fear cannot but be tightly related</_>
                </_>
            </present>
        </temporal_aspects>
    </rational_interpretation>



<donative_interpretation cog:lid='donative'>
    My fear is that I am proving to be unworthy of my most valued gift, and of the gift giver
    <gift_conditions>
        To prove worthy of a gift of value, one must prove equal to it
        <_>
            To prove worthy of a gift, one must prove equal to the task of holding on to it
            </_>
        <_>
            To prove worthy of a gift of value, one must properly express one’s gratitude for it
            </_>
        <childhood_remembrance cog:link='/poet/conditions_of_a_gift/#remembrance'/>
        <affective_image cog:link='/poet/conditions_of_a_gift/#story'/>
        </gift_conditions>
    <valued_gift>
        <_ cog:link='/theorist/ethics/moral_matter/#R'/>
        <_>
            Practical reason is a gift
            <_>
                Practical reason implies ‘heaven in corporeal’
                <aesthetic_access cog:link='/poet/reason_as_heaven/#story'/>
                </_>
            <_>
                The offer of practical reason is written in the night sky like a covenant
                <_ cog:link='/theorist/ethics/moral_matter/#X'/>
                </_>
            </_>
        </valued_gift>
    <_>I have not proven that I am equal to practical reason</_>
    <_ cog:link='#experience'/>
    </donative_interpretation>



